            {
              "kind": "narrator",
              "path": "/people/narrators/19",
              "text": "أَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام )"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " قَالَ"
            }
          ],
          "text": "عِدَّةٌ مِنْ أَصْحَابِنَا عَنْ أَحْمَدَ بْنِ أَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ عَنْ أَبِيهِ عَنْ سُلَيْمَانَ بْنِ جَعْفَرٍ الْجَعْفَرِيِّ عَمَّنْ ذَكَرَهُ عَنْ أَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) قَالَ"
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:3:2:1",
        "text": [
          " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) مَا رَأَيْتُ مِنْ ضَعِيفَاتِ الدِّينِ وَ نَاقِصَاتِ الْعُقُولِ أَسْلَبَ لِذِي لُبٍّ مِنْكُنَّ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Abu Abdullah, from his father, from Suleyman Bin Ja’far Al Ja’fary, from the one who mentioned it, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘I<sup>saww</sup> have not seen from the weak ones of the Religion, and the deficient of the intellects, ones with a stiff heart more than you (women)’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "1. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn abu ‘Abd Allah from his father from Sulayman ibn Ja’far al-Ja’fariy from those whom he has mentioned who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that the Messenger of Allah, O Allah, grant compensation to Muhammad and his family worthy of their services to Your cause, has said, ‘I never saw anyone more snatching from an intelligent person, than these weak in religion, deficient of reason; you women are.’” "
          ]
        }
      },
